PREP: 10 minutes
COOK: 12 minutes
YIELD: 6 pieces

INGREDIENTS:
1 baguette
Roasted tomato sauce
Mozzarella (fresh or shredded)
Cherry tomatoes, quartered
Red onion, sliced
Fresh basil ribbons
Salt and pepper
Dried oregano
Fresh garlic, sliced thin
Red pepper flakes
Olive oil
Reduced balsamic vinegar (optional)

DIRECTIONS:
Preheat oven to 425&deg;F.
Slice the baguette into thirds, then halve longways to make six equal pieces.
Drizzle baguette slices with olive oil, then toast until beginning to turn golden around the edges, about 5 minutes.
Top with sauce, mozarella, tomatoes, red onion slices, and garlic.
Bake for 7 minutes.
If desired, serve with balsamic vinegar drizzled over the top.

NOTES:
If you're using fresh mozarella, use less than you think you need.

